      ],
      "ety": "[OE. slow, slaw, AS. slāw; akin to OS. slēu blunt, dull, D. sleeuw, slee, sour, OHG. slēo blunt, dull, Icel. slōr, slær, Dan. slöv, Sw. slö. Cf. Sloe, and Sloth.]",
      "sources": [
        "1913 Webster"
      ],
      "morph": null,
      "usage": [
        "Slow, Tardy, Dilatory. Slow is the wider term, denoting either a want of rapid motion or inertness of intellect. Dilatory signifies a proneness to defer, a habit of delaying the performance of what we know must be done. Tardy denotes the habit of being behind hand; as, tardy in making up one's acounts."
      ],
      "wordforms": [],
      "entry_synonyms": [],
      "entry_fields": [],
      "senses": [
        {
          "sn": "1.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "Moving a short space in a relatively long time; not swift; not quick in motion; not rapid; moderate; deliberate; as, a slow stream; a slow motion."
          ],
          "quotes": [],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "2.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "Not happening in a short time; gradual; late."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "These changes in the heavens, though slow, produced Like change on sea and land, sidereal blast."
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "3.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "Not ready; not prompt or quick; dilatory; sluggish; as, slow of speech, and slow of tongue."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "Fixed on defense, the Trojans are not slow To guard their shore from an expected foe."
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "4.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "Not hasty; not precipitate; acting with deliberation; tardy; inactive."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "He that is slow to wrath is of great understanding."
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "5.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "Behind in time; indicating a time earlier than the true time; as, the clock or watch is slow."
          ],
          "quotes": [],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "6.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "Not advancing or improving rapidly; as, the slow growth of arts and sciences."
          ],
          "quotes": [],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "7.",
          "fields": [
            "(Zool.)"
          ],
          "defs": [
            "Heavy in wit; not alert, prompt, or spirited; wearisome; dull."
          ],
          "quotes": [],
          "notes": [
            "☞ Slow is often used in the formation of compounds for the most part self-explaining; as, slow-gaited, slow-paced, slow-sighted, slow-winged, and the like."
          ],
